CMake suite maintained and supported by Kitware (kitware.com/cmake).

  • cmake output:
    Do you mean the file CMakeCache.txt ？

I actually use the command ccmake ../, press c for compiling and g for generating, after pressing g, I got the above 2 ERROR messages:

CMake Error: install(EXPORT "Caffe2Targets" ...) includes target "caffe2" which requires target "nnpack" that is not in the export set.

CMake Error: install(EXPORT "Caffe2Targets" ...) includes target "caffe2" which requires target "cpuinfo" that is not in the export set.

body:
@pjh5 

- Ubuntu 18.04

- $ cmake --version
cmake version 3.10.2

CMake suite maintained and supported by Kitware (kitware.com/cmake).

- cmake output:
Do you mean the file CMakeCache.txt ？ 

I actually use the command `ccmake ../`, press **c** for compiling and **g** for generating, after pressing **g**, I got the above **2 ERROR** messages:

>  CMake Error: install(EXPORT "Caffe2Targets" ...) includes target "caffe2" which requires target "nnpack" that is not in the export set.
> 
>  CMake Error: install(EXPORT "Caffe2Targets" ...) includes target "caffe2" which requires target "cpuinfo" that is not in the export set.
